print Goal
Sprint Goal:
Implement the core Pixel Art Generator pipeline, enabling users to upload an image and convert it into retro-style pixel art using either the CPU or the simulated GPU processing mode.
Mini-ADR
Decision: Implement a hybrid CPU/GPU workflow where the CPU manages image loading and control flow, while the simulated GPU performs parallel color quantization and pixel-block computation.
Reason: This structure demonstrates the performance difference and architectural separation between sequential (CPU) and parallel (GPU-style) processing.
Consequence: The system gains improved performance for large images, but requires additional logic to coordinate CPU/GPU modes and maintain consistent output across both paths.
Mini-API Description
Endpoint: POST /api/pixelate
Request: { "image": "<binary>", "mode": "cpu" | "gpu", "pixelSize": 8 }
Success: 200 OK with { "pixelArtImage": "<base64>" }
Fail: 400 Bad Request with { "error": "invalid image or parameters" }
Description: Converts an uploaded image into pixel art using either CPU mode or simulated GPU mode for processing.
